Headquarters Regions: East Coast, New England, Northeastern US
Full Description: In a sentence: Discover and vote for the local ‘Must Try’ businesses in your city. MustTryIt.com - is a mobile website that enables users to browse local ‘musty try’ businesses in their city - vote for the ones they love, and discover new ones they didn’t even know about. The real benefit is that people get a chance to make a connection with the local small business owners they can trust, so they feel like they’ve got a friend in the business. We want to help make every day be like Small Business Saturday. By helping connect deserving local businesses with these buy-local-minded people, we believe they are more likely to keep their dollars local when they have a connection and a friend in the business. Obviously, not every local business qualifies as a “must try" in people’s minds, just like not every team will make the playoffs. It can be hard to know who to trust when you do business locally. We want to fix that. We believe there are six qualities that separate unremarkable businesses from "must try" businesses. Our mission is to save Main Street, by enabling connections between local shoppers and deserving small businesses. That means helping small businesses become more meaningfully unique, worth talking about, and easier to refer.

Full Description: Specialty Indian Foods Enterprise, Inc. stands as a distinctive force in the realm of wholesale food distribution. Situated in the bustling center of New York, this establishment caters exclusively to the discerning demands of Indian restaurants spanning the expansive Tristate region, encompassing New York, New Jersey, Connecticut, and Philadelphia. Their overarching mission is both resolute and impactful: to furnish restaurants with premium-grade ingredients that have the power to transform everyday meals into epicurean delights. Recognizing that the essence of exceptional Indian cuisine lies within the quality of its constituents, Specialty Indian Foods Enterprise, Inc. boasts an extensive inventory encompassing an array of aromatic spices, fragrant rice, nourishing legumes, flavorful pulses, essential oils, frozen delicacies, and even vital kitchen supplies, including plastic items. Their meticulously curated selection showcases products sourced from distinguished brands, ensuring access to the most exquisite offerings available. At Specialty Indian Foods Enterprise, Inc., their commitment to ensuring customer satisfaction remains unwavering. They take pride in providing competitive pricing, exceptional customer service, and swift, dependable deliveries. Their triumph is intricately tied to the prosperity of their clientele, and they leave no stone unturned in supporting restaurants throughout their culinary endeavors. In their capacity as distributors, Specialty Indian Foods Enterprise, Inc. proudly represents a variety of esteemed brands within the sphere of Indian gastronomy. Their distribution network spans the Tristate area, where they dutifully serve Indian dining establishments with unwavering dedication and meticulousness. Whether catering to a bustling eatery in the heart of New York City or a cozy, family-owned restaurant nestled in the corners of New Jersey, Specialty Indian Foods Enterprise, Inc. remains a steadfast source for premium Indian ingredients. The exploration of specialty Indian cuisine at Specialty Indian Foods Enterprise, Inc. is deeply rooted in a commitment to both well-being and culinary distinction. Spearheading this journey is Dr. Jannat Chowdhury, a Board Certified Naturopathic Doctor with a profound background in healthcare. Recognizing the pivotal role of food in overall health, Dr. Chowdhury draws inspiration from the timeless wisdom of Hippocrates, who famously espoused, "Let Food Be Thy Medicine, And Let Thy Medicine Be Food." With a firm belief in harnessing the therapeutic potential of Indian spices, herbs, and ingredients, Dr. Chowdhury advocates for the merits of staples such as turmeric (curcumin), cumin, fenugreek (methi), cardamom, clove, ginger, garlic, and more. These quintessential components, integral to every Indian dish, not only tantalize the taste buds but also proffer remarkable health benefits. Dr. Chowdhury's vision is both lucid and transformative: to promote well-being through nourishing sustenance. Her ardor for wholesome and flavorsome cuisine harmoniously aligns with the mission of Specialty Indian Foods Enterprise, Inc. Together, they remain committed to aiding restaurant owners in providing exceptional culinary experiences to their patrons, infused with the opulence of Indian gastronomy. In collaboration with Specialty Indian Foods Enterprise, Inc., one embarks on a sensory journey through flavors, distinction, and authenticity, setting new benchmarks for dining establishments and solidifying their position as dependable suppliers, culinary partners, and gateways to the vibrant realm of Indian gastronomy.
